#Text=Moreton Island
#Text=Moreton
#Text=Island
#Text=is a large sand island , 36 km long , covering 17,500 ha , only 35 km off Brisbane forming the eastern boundary of the Moreton Bay Marine Park .
#Text=Understand
#Text=Moreton Island is 98 % National Park protecting its unique vegetation , wildlife , freshwater lakes and streams and its magnificent coastal sand dunes .
#Text=There are 3 townships located on the western side of the island each providing a different experience and facilities .
#Text=Bulwer is a holiday village geared to deal with the travellers who arrive on the island and require food , bait and supplies .
#Text=There is a small convenience and liquor store ( licensed ) , taxi service , public phone and bait and tackle shop at the northern end of the township .
#Text=Cowan Cowan is a quiet residential township with several places to stay , mainly holiday houses and fishing cabins .
#Text=The township has no through traffic in town and a vehicle free beach making it a popular spot for families with small children .
#Text=It was originally established as a military camp in 1938 and housed approx 1000 soldiers during the military occupation of Moreton Island .
#Text=Remains of military buildings such as gun emplacements and forts can still be seen on the beach in front of Cowan Cowan and are a reminder of Australia 's involvement in WWII .
#Text=Kooringal is famous for The Gutter Bar and Toulkerrie oyster farm .
#Text=The village consists of a number of private holiday homes and a few fishing clubhouses scattered along the beachfront and separated by sand tracks and Island vegetation .
#Text=This township has its own airstrip and is serviced by a vehicular barge that runs from Amity Point on North Stradbroke Island .
#Text=Tangalooma is famous for the Tangalooma Island Resort ( formerly known as Tangalooma Wild Dolphin Resort ) but now there are private homes located atop the hill behind the resort .

#Text=The resort was the site of Queensland 's only whaling station , with humpback whales being harvested on their annual migration north between 1952 and 1962 , The flensing plan of the station still exists as part of the resort .
#Text=Ferry
#Text=Most people access the Island via ferry .
#Text=Ferries for vehicles and passengers run daily .
#Text=Amity Trader , ☏ +61487227437 .
#Text=From Stradbroke Island to Kooringal . 20 min transit , day return from $ 20 .
#Text=MICAT Ferry , ☏ +61739093333 .
#Text=From Port of Brisbane ( Brisbane River southside ) to Tangalooma Wrecks .
#Text=Daily in peak periods , twice on Fridays and twice on Sundays .
#Text=No service on Tuesdays in off-peak period .
#Text=Tangalooma Island Resort , ☏ +61732686333 .
#Text=From Pinkenba ( Brisbane River northside ) to Tangalooma Resort .
#Text=3-4 runs daily .
#Text=Return Day Cruises and Guest accommodation transfers .
#Text=Private boat access
#Text=It is possible to travel in your own vessel , although there are no public mooring available at Moreton Island .
#Text=Tangalooma Wrecks can be a safe anchorage .
#Text=Get around
#Text=One of the most enjoyable ways to visit Moreton Island is by four wheel drive ( 4WD ) vehicle .
#Text=4WD vehicles are essential for driving on the island .
#Text=All vehicles must be registered and have a valid Moreton Island Recreation Area vehicle access permit .
#Text=Moreton Island Tourist Services , ☏ +61734082261 .

#Text=For those who do not have a 4wd there is a 4WD Taxi Service , based at Bulwer that can take you anywhere in the National Park or to accommodation at Tangalooma or in the townships of Bulwer and Cowan-Cowan .
#Text=See
#Text=See dolphins , turtles , dugongs , plenty of fish life
#Text=North Point has " The Champagne Pools " a natural ocean pool hollowed out amongst the rocks ,
#Text=Honeymoon Bay
#Text=The Cape Moreton Light House
#Text=Blue Lagoon a natural fresh water lake
#Text=The Tangalooma and Bulwer Wrecks deliberately sunken ships form incredible artificial reefs , featuring an abundance of marine life and good snorkeling .
#Text=Tangalooma Island Resort was originally established as a whaling station
#Text=Cowan Cowan a coastal defence bases from World War II has relics as a reminder of Australia 's involvement in WWII
#Text=Bulwer provides panoramic views back to the mainland and the Glass House Mountains .
#Text=The Grave sites still standing after over 100 years from people passing through the bay .
#Text=Do
#Text=Humpback whale watching off Cape Moreton move through moreton bay on their annual migration from June to November .
#Text=4WD down the Surfside , a long 40 km stretch of white sandy beach , pass trough the thick bush of the Moreton Island National Park .
#Text=Go fishing , swimming in fresh or saltwater .
#Text=Snorkel or dive .
#Text=The Tangalooma wrecks , Sherubs Cave , Hutchinson Shoal or Flinders reef which are full of marine and fish life .
#Text=Beach sports
#Text=Bushwalking campfires and star gazing .
#Text=Sand boarding down some of the world 's highest coastal sandhills .
#Text=Feed the wild Dolphins .
#Text=Walk up Mount Tempest the highest sand dune in the world .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Beach House Rotunda Restaurant , Beach Cafe , Tursiops Buffet Restaurant , Tangalooma Coffee Shop , Whalers Bar , Tangalooma Convenience Store , Tangalooma .
#Text=Beach House Rotunda Restaurant features fresh produce including MSA grade Black Angus steak , local seafood , vegetarian and halal options .
#Text=Beach Cafe serves Fish & Chips , pizzas , burgers , salads , and light meals for outdoor beachfront dining or takeaway .
#Text=Both are open daily for lunch and dinner servicing accommodation guests , and day-cruise guests of Tangalooma Island Resort .
#Text=Tursiops Buffet Restaurant has casual buffet dining , and is open for breakfast & lunch daily ( and dinner on most Saturday nights ) .
#Text=Tangalooma Coffee Shop offers desserts , sandwiches , wraps , sushi , hot pies and sausage rolls , in addition to coffee , and is open daily .
#Text=The Whalers Bar serves a wide range of cocktails and other beverages and has a pool table , with take away food available .
#Text=There is also a convenience store in Tanglooma .
#Text=Gutter Bar , Kooringal .
#Text=Provides seafood , meat , meals and other services for the local area .
#Text=Renowned across the island for their seafood that is fresh from the local trawlers and oysters from the clear local waters .
#Text=A great way to end the day with a fresh beverage .
#Text=Sleep
#Text=There is a range of holiday accommodation on Moreton Island at all the towns .
#Text=Moreton Island provides a variety of coastal camping experiences , some accessible by 4WD , others accessible by boat or close to barge landing points .
#Text=You will need a vehicle access permit to drive on Moreton Island .
#Text=Preferably bring a fuel stove .
#Text=Bring your own firewood ,
#Text=Moreton Island Adventures Accommodation ( Castaways Restaurant & Convenience Store ) , ☏ +61739093333 , ✉ booking@moretonislandadventures.com.au .
#Text=Moreton Island Adventures have multiple accommodation offerings available - units , glamping , camping and dorms .
#Text=MIA also operate the ' Castaways Restaurant ' , in Bulwer .
#Text=It is a licensed venue which offers meals , coffee , drinks and desserts in a relaxed garden setting , under a thatched roof .
#Text=There is a convenience store attached to the restaurant which stocks most island necessities .
#Text=The store and restaurant are contactable on 07 3408 2202 or via castaways@moretonislandadventures.com.au.
